author: Mark Hinog
title: Matthew Dellavedova's hustle leads to him chilling uncomfortably on the scoring table
text: At Sunday’s Milwaukee Bucks game, Matthew Dellavedova had a little too much hustle. Delly swatted the ball away from the Phoenix Suns’ Eric Bledsoe, which led to him chasing the ball in an attempt to keep it inside the court. Consequently, it also led to Delly jumping onto the scoring table and chilling for a bit, while his teammates got him out.
